### NOTES & DOCUMENTATION

# 1. FILE UPLOADS LIMITATION:
#    VS Code REST Client has limited support for file uploads.
#    For testing file uploads (endpoint #2), we recommend:
#    - Postman: Import this file, easier file upload UI
#    - Thunder Client: VS Code extension with better file support
#    - cURL: Command line alternative

# 2. FILE UPLOAD TESTING WITH POSTMAN:
#    a. Import this file to Postman (File → Import → Raw text)
#    b. For endpoint #2, switch Body to "form-data"
#    c. Add fields:
#       - registrationNumber (text): AB12CDE
#       - vehicleColour (text): Blue
#       - vehicleMake (text): TOYOTA
#       - vehicleYear (text): 2020
#       - hasValidInsurance (text): true
#       - isRoadworthy (text): true
#       - hasPermission (text): true
#       - vehiclePhotos (file): Select 4 images
#       - insuranceCertificate (file): Select 1 PDF

# 3. FILE UPLOAD TESTING WITH CURL:
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/verification/taxi/apply \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN" \
  -F "registrationNumber=AB12CDE" \
  -F "vehicleColour=Blue" \
  -F "vehicleMake=TOYOTA" \
  -F "vehicleYear=2020" \
  -F "hasValidInsurance=true" \
  -F "isRoadworthy=true" \
  -F "hasPermission=true" \
  -F "vehiclePhotos=@./test-files/vehicle-front.jpg" \
  -F "vehiclePhotos=@./test-files/vehicle-side.jpg" \
  -F "vehiclePhotos=@./test-files/vehicle-rear.jpg" \
  -F "vehiclePhotos=@./test-files/vehicle-interior.jpg" \
  -F "insuranceCertificate=@./test-files/insurance.pdf"

# 4. AUTHENTICATION FLOW:
#    a. Register: POST /users/register
#    b. Verify email: POST /users/verify-email
#    c. Verify phone: POST /users/verify-phone
#    d. Verify identity: POST /verification/identity/upload (with driving license)
#    e. Login: POST /users/login (get JWT token)
#    f. Use token in Authorization header for driver endpoints

# 5. SMART HYBRID VALIDATION:
#    - Step 1: User only sees registration, tax, MOT status
#    - Step 2: User must answer colour/make/year (security questions)
#    - Backend compares answers with DVLA data
#    - Prevents fraud: User must have physical access to vehicle

# 6. APPLICATION STATUSES:
#    - pending_admin_review: Waiting for admin to review
#    - approved: Driver verified, can activate driver mode
#    - rejected: Application rejected, can re-apply after fixing issues

# 7. REQUIRED FILES:
#    Vehicle Photos (4 required):
#    - Front view
#    - Side view
#    - Rear view
#    - Interior view
#    Format: JPEG/PNG, max 10MB each
#
#    Insurance Certificate (1 required):
#    - Current insurance policy
#    Format: PDF, max 10MB

# 8. DVLA/MOT CHECKS:
#    Automatic checks performed:
#    - DVLA: Tax status, vehicle details, registration validity
#    - MOT: Test history, expiry date, mileage, defects
#    - Both must pass for application to proceed

# 9. ADMIN WORKFLOW:
#    a. View pending applications (future endpoint)
#    b. Review vehicle photos
#    c. Verify insurance certificate
#    d. Check DVLA/MOT results
#    e. Approve or reject with reason

# 10. TESTING CHECKLIST:
#     Before testing, ensure you have:
#     [ ] Test DVLA API key in .env
#     [ ] Test MOT API key in .env
#     [ ] AWS S3 credentials in .env
#     [ ] Test image files (4 JPEGs)
#     [ ] Test PDF file (1 insurance doc)
#     [ ] User with verified identity (driving license)
#     [ ] Valid JWT tokens (user + admin)

# 11. ERROR HANDLING:
#     Common errors and solutions:
#     - 400: Check request format, required fields
#     - 401: Token expired or missing
#     - 403: User not verified or not admin
#     - 404: Vehicle not found or user not found
#     - 500: Check API keys, S3 credentials, logs

# 12. RATE LIMITS (Recommended Implementation):
#     - Check vehicle: 10 req/hour per user
#     - Submit application: 1 req/day per user
#     - Status check: 60 req/hour per user
#     - Admin endpoints: 100 req/hour

# 13. PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT:
#     Update these for production:
#     @baseUrl = https://api.rideandpark.com
#     Use production API keys
#     Use production S3 bucket
#     Enable HTTPS only
#     Set up proper CORS

# 14. SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS:
#     - Files stored privately in S3 (not public)
#     - API keys never exposed to frontend
#     - Admin endpoints require admin role
#     - User can only access their own data
#     - Input validation on all fields
#     - File type and size validation

# 15. MONITORING & LOGGING:
#     Log these events:
#     - Vehicle check requests
#     - Application submissions
#     - Admin decisions (approve/reject)
#     - Failed DVLA/MOT checks
#     - File upload errors
#     - Security violations

# 16. ADMIN DECISION FIELDS:
#     For approval:
#     - userId: required (string)
#     - decision: required ("approve")
#     - reason: NOT included (will be ignored if provided)
#
#     For rejection:
#     - userId: required (string)
#     - decision: required ("reject")
#     - reason: REQUIRED (string, min 10 characters)
#     - Must explain why application was rejected
#     - User will see this reason in their status check